comment:
* ChildSaProposal represents a proposed configuration to negotiate a Child SA. * *

ChildSaProposal will contain cryptograhic algorithms and key generation materials for the * negotiation of a Child SA. * *

User must provide at least one valid ChildSaProposal when they are creating a new Child SA. * * @see RFC 7296, Internet Key Exchange * Protocol Version 2 (IKEv2)

methods.name: public static ChildSaProposal fromPersistableBundle(@NonNull PersistableBundle in)

methods.name: public static Set<Integer> getSupportedEncryptionAlgorithms()
methods.comment:
* Returns supported encryption algorithms for Child SA proposal negotiation. * *

Some algorithms may not be supported on old devices.

methods.name: public static Set<Integer> getSupportedIntegrityAlgorithms()
methods.comment:

Some algorithms may not be supported on old devices.
